SIMPLE: eightieth
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Eightieth
<hw>Eight"i*eth</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Eighty</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The next in order after
seventy-ninth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Consisting of one of eighty equal parts or
divisions.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eightieth</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Eightieth
<hw>Eight"i*eth</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quotient of a unit divided
by eighty; one of eighty equal parts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eightling</ent>⟦br⟧
